<h2>DirectorySource&lt;T&gt;</h2>
<p>A directory source specifies directory paths to create a modules from. 
The directory paths are relative to the application root directory.</p>
<p>The <code>FilePattern</code> property is a semicolon separated string that defines which file types to include in the modules.</p>
<p>The optional <code>Exclude</code> property is a regular expression used to exclude files.</p>
<p>Here's an example:</p>
<pre><code>moduleConfiguration.Add(
    <span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="code-type">DirectorySource</span>&lt;<span class="code-type">ScriptModule</span>&gt;(<span class="string">"Scripts/lib"</span>, <span class="string">"Scripts/app"</span>)
    {
        FilePattern = <span class="string">"*.js;*.coffee"</span>,
        Exclude = <span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="code-type">Regex</span>(<span class="string">"-vsdoc\\.js$"</span>) <span class="comment">// Excludes the VS documentation files</span>
        SearchOption = <span class="code-type">SearchOption</span>.TopDirectoryOnly <span class="comment">// The default is AllDirectories</span>
    }
);</code></pre>